///

///Description
@node "Description"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Status"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}What is it:@{uu}@{ub}

   AmigaOS 35 is a  Bootscreen for Rainboot2. With  Rainboot you  can  Display
   a Picture, playing sound fx, music and Anims by booting your Amiga Computer.

@endnode
///
/// Requirements
@node "Requirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Description"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}What Do You need.:@{uu}@{ub}

   · @{b}An Amiga or Amiga compat. Computer System@{ub}, (with a correct instal-
     lation of OS3.x (in a logical way OS35))
   · @{b}Rainboot2 Bootsoftware@{ub} (best, actual Version 2.90 (06.09.2000)).
   · @{b}Good handling of Workbench and AmigaOS@{ub}



   You don't have Rainboot2 ?  Download  it  from  Aminet,  or  visit  the
   Homepage of Andreas Falkenhahn.

   @{b}Address@{ub}: http://www.home.pages.de/~Airsoft



   @{apen 2}@{bpen 3} Warning: @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   Do  not  use  a  unregistrate  Version  of  Rainboot2.  You  can   have
   Disharmonies with the Bootconfig, please let you now register.

@endnode
///
/// Installation
@node "Installation"
@next "Edit"
@prev "Requirements"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}Place for Data:@{uu}@{ub}

   @{b}1.@{ub} Open  the  Configs  Directory  of  extracted  AmigaOS 35  Bootscreen
      Systems, and Open the Configs Directory of your  Installt  Rainboot2
      Systems.

   @{b}2.@{ub} Now copy via Drag & Drop a drawer e.g. aos35_640x480 to your Configs
      Directory of  Installt  Rainboot  System. You  can rename the copied
      drawer e.g. "OS35Boot".

   @{b}3.@{ub} Copy XHelvetica Directory, XHelvetica.font to "sys:fonts/"
      (This font have a small modification to Original XHelvetica.font
      this character ¦ is one Pixel set up - that's all).

   @{b}4.@{ub} Installation Done.

   @{b}5.@{ub} @{" edit " link "Edit"} your startup-sequence

@endnode

@node "Edit"
@next "Course"
@prev "Installation"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}Edit your startup-sequence:@{uu}@{ub}

   Edit your startup-sequence, run  the  Rainboot2  command  direct  under
   "c:conclip" of your startup-sequence.

   @{b}c:rainboot2@{ub} @{FG fill}>nil:@{FG text} @{FG shine}<path>AmigaOS35.config@{FG text} @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x00039024 @{b}QUIET@{ub}

   You must give a correct ModeID, best, the same ID  of  your  Workbench,
   you can do this with the tool GetModeID, you can finde GetModeID in the
   tools Directory of Rainbbot2. Run it and Click in  the  Requester  your
   Screen  Resolution.  GetModeID  give you now your Hex ModeID. Please do
   not play with ModeID's. Use Only a ModeID for your Screen !



   @{u}MODEID's for some Standard AGA Resolutions:@{uu}

   @{b}DBLNTSC@{ub}:  HighRes flimmerfrei               640x400:  @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x00099004
   @{b}NTSC@{ub}:     HighRes interlace                 640x400:  @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x00019004

   @{b}Multiscan Produktivity:@{ub}                     640x480:  @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x00039024

   @{b}DBLPAL@{ub}:   HighRes flimmerfrei               640x512:  @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x000A9004
   @{b}PAL@{ub}:      HighRes Interlace                 640x512:  @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x00029004

   @{b}Super72@{ub}:  Super HighRes Interlace           800x600:  @{b}MODEID@{ub}=0x00089024



   @{apen 2}@{bpen 3} Note: @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}

   At the Moment i can't give helps and  support  for  Gfx-card  users.  I
   don't  have  a  Gfx-card,  you  must self find out Your MODEID for Your
   Gfx-card Resolution. And don't  forget  "RTG"  Argument  behind  MODEID
   Argument.

@endnode
///
/// Course
@node "Course"
@next "Proplems"
@prev "Installation"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}Course of Bootaccess:@{uu}@{ub}

   You have the Installation corrected  done'ed, now read the short course
   of Bootaccess.

   Boot your Amiga Computer, firstly You have a black Screen, seconds a go
   You see the aos35 background he fade'ed to You. In the  Background  You
   hear playing the Music, quietly. At the right You seeing the  Date  and
   Time  (only in 800x600 resolution config). Left from Time You  see  the
   AmigaBall, he is animated. All coming up's have a fx-ping.
   Now begins the Processbar Moving with a fx-ping on the left of  Screen,
   the  Processbar  have short stops, this is right. Is the Process at the
   end, by Done, you have fx-ping too. Is the Bootprocess end'ed, now  the
   Screen is cleared of printed types with fx-pings. At the and You have a
   fade to white and in the next a fade to black, and the last fade  bring
   up Your Workbench. That's all ...

@endnode
///
/// Proplems
@node "Proplems"
@next "Timeing"
@prev "Course"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}What the hell:@{uu}@{ub}

   · Have You all Installation points understanded an right set'ed ?
   · Have You the startup-sequence corrected write'ed ?

   Now going all this points through again. Is the Problem definitivly  by
   my  Config  contact  @{" me " link "Author"}.  It is possible the Rainboot2 have Bugs. At
   this  Momment  you  must  contact  the  Author  of  Rainboot2,  Andreas
   Falkenhahn.

   (email-Adresse of Andreas Falkenhahn:  @{b}Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de@{ub}).

   
   · @{" Timeing " link "timeing"} Proplems with Processbar speed.

@endnode

@node "Timeing"
@next "faq"
@prev "Proplems"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}Proplem, prozessbar Timeing:@{uu}@{ub}

   You have speed Proplems? You must set  a  other  speed  for  processbar
   print. See the marked string, and give a new integer.



   See here "AmigaOS35.config" cutting

   @{apen 2}@{bpen 1}Cutting begin                                                          @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}

   %SN2C1 %AL
   %SN4C2V15L

   %D30 %D0
   %X66 %Y530 %C139 %RB %RS255 %SN2C1 Loading %D0 ¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦
   %D20 %D0
   %X66 %Y530 %C255 %RB %RS139 %SN1C1 Loading @{apen 2}@{bpen 3}%D5@{apen 1}@{bpen 0} ¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦¦

   @{apen 2}@{bpen 1}Cutting end                                                            @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}


   
   Set @{apen 2}@{bpen 3}%D5@{apen 1}@{bpen 0} down to 4 or lower, is Your Amiga Boot at  the  end,  but  your
   Processbar is not by Done.

   @{b}so@{ub}: @{apen 2}@{bpen 3}%D4@{apen 1}@{bpen 0} ¦¦¦¦¦¦ ...

   or

   Set @{apen 2}@{bpen 3}%D5@{apen 1}@{bpen 0} up to 6 or higher, is Your Amiga Boot not on  ending,  but  the
   Processbar  is  alot  of  seconds  by  Done.  Have  you a extremly long
   Boottime set it to 7 or 8.

   @{b}so@{ub}: @{apen 2}@{bpen 3}%D6@{apen 1}@{bpen 0} ¦¦¦¦¦¦ etc.

@endnode
///
/// FAQ's
@node "faq"
@next "History"
@prev "Proplems"
@toc "main"

   @{b}@{u}Ask and Question:@{uu}@{ub}

   At this Site You can Read the Asks and Questions, which some User have.



   @{apen 1}@{bpen 2}Ask:     @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   @{i}Why given't a Bootscreen with Hardware informations, like my  CPU  type
   or my RAM capacity etc@{ui}.

   @{apen 2}@{bpen 1}Question:@{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   I don't want made this. Such information  prints  overloaded  even  the
   Bootscreen.  It  is  not really important. Important is only where your
   Amiga Computer at the time is, the show over  the  Bootprocess  status.
   How  long  i  must  wait to see for my Workbench Screen. The Processbar
   looks like fine over the Bootprocess. I can make this, but  it  is  not
   planed for the future to build in, such prints.



   @{apen 1}@{bpen 2}Ask:     @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   @{i}I have tune'ed My Workbench Screen, My Standard Resolution  is  "DBLPAL
   HighRes flickerfree" 640x512. I tund'ed these with the Preferences tool
   Overscan to 659x527, now i have a bigger Workbench size, this  make  Me
   happy.  Now  Can  You  made  for  Me  a  special Bootscreen, for My new
   Overscan'ed 659x527 Workbench !?@{ui}

   @{apen 2}@{bpen 1}Question:@{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   This make You happy, so so ... But this make me not happy ! In the past
   some  users  contacted  me  with this asks. For the future I can't made
   hundred's of special Bootconfigs,  i  don't  have  any  time  for  this
   working  !  Well  users, please used Standard prefered Resolutions. The
   Preferences tool Overscan is only imaginary for centering for a lot  of
   Monitortypes.  Or  for Special Video or Gameprojects, but not for nasty
   Workbench Resolution patching.



   @{apen 1}@{bpen 2}Ask:     @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   @{i}I have a Gfx-card and I used a Resolution with 1024x768 pixels. Can You
   Supported this Resolution, or other higher standard Resolutions ?@{ui}

   @{apen 2}@{bpen 1}Question:@{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   Yes, I made this, in the future i supported this or higher Resolutions,
   but  at  this time i can't made. At the moment i don't have a Gfx-card.
   You must even wait for this Screens.



   @{apen 1}@{bpen 2}Ask:     @{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   @{i}Your Bootscreens are nice, but i find  Bootscreen like Star Trek really
   better.  Can  You  made a Special Star Trek Bootscreen with the biggest
   Klingon Logo, which the Human race ever seen !?@{ui}

   @{apen 2}@{bpen 1}Question:@{apen 1}@{bpen 0}
   No, for such Fu'Manchu Idears, i'am not to  have.  I  Constructed  only
   Neutral  and  Professional  Boot  Screens,  which  in mind to the Amiga
   Computer. Star Trek is an alternative theme, and don't have any  thinks
   to  the  AMIGA  (yes  i'am a big fan of science-fiction, but don't even
   Star Trek tingel-tangel themes). You can visit the Homepage of  Andreas
   Falkenhahn  (or  in the Aminet), which made Rainboot2, of this Page you
   can  find   many  Bootconfigs  in  the  Download  section,  with   such
   alternative themes. Star Trek too.

   @{b}Adresse@{ub}: http://www.home.pages.de/~Airsoft

@endnode
